B040C001V001	40	1	1	A record of descent of Jesus Anointed, son of David, son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham begot the Isaac, Isaac and begot the Jacob, Jacob and begot the Judas and the brothers of him.
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Judas and begot the Phares and the Zara by the Thamar. Phares and begot the Esrom; Esrom and begot the Aram;
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Aram and begot the Aminadab; Aminadab and begot the Naasson; Naasson and begot the Salmon;
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmon and begot the Booz by the Rachab; Booz and begot the Obed by the Ruth; Obed and begot the Jesse.
B040C001V006	40	1	6	Jesse and begot the David the king. David the king and begot the Solomon by the of the Urias;
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Solomon and begot the Roboam; Roboam and begot the Abia; Abia and begot the Asa;
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asa and begot the Josaphat; Josaphat and begot the Joram; Joram and begot the Ozias;
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Ozias and begot the Jotham; Jotham and begot the Achaz; Achaz and begot the Ezekias;
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Ezekias and begot the Manasses; Manasses and begot the Amon; Amon and begot the Josias;
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Josias and begot the Jechonias and the brothers of him, near the removal Babylonian.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	After the removal Babylonian, Jechonias begot the Salathiel. Salathiel and begot the Zorobabel;
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zorobabel and begot the Abiud; Abiud and begot the Eliakim; Eliakim and begot the Azor;
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Azor and begot the Sadok; Sadok and begot the Achim; Achim and begot the Eliud;
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Eliud and begot the Eleazar; Eleazar and begot the Matthan; Matthan and begot the Jacob;
B040C001V016	40	1	16	Jacob and begot the Joseph, the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, that being named Anointed.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	All then the generations from Abraham till David, generations fourteen; and from David till the removal Babylonian, generations fourteen; and from the removal of Babylonian till Anointed, generations fourteen.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	Of the now Jesus Anointed the birth thus was. Being espoused for the mother of him Mary to the Joseph, before either came together them, she was found in womb having by a spirit holy.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Joseph and the husband of her, a just man being and not willing her to publicly expose, was inclined secretly to release her.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	These but of him thinking on, lo a messenger of a Lord in a dream appeared to him, saying: Joseph, son of David, not thou shouldst fear to take Mary the wife of thee; that for in her being found, by a spirit is holy;
B040C001V021	40	1	21	she shall bear and a son, and thou shalt call the name of him Jesus; he for shall save the people of him from the sins of them;
B040C001V022	40	1	22	(This and all was done, so that might be fulfilled the word spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying:
B040C001V023	40	1	23	Lo, the virgin in womb shall have, and shall bear a son, and they shall call the name of him Emmanuel; which is being translated, with us a God.)
B040C001V024	40	1	24	Being aroused and the Joseph from the sleep, he did as commanded to him the messenger of a Lord, and took the wife of him,
B040C001V025	40	1	25	but not he knew her till she brought forth the a son of her the first born; and called the name of him Jesus.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	The and Jesus being born in Bethleem of the Judea, in days of Herod the king, lo, wiseman from an east country came into Jerusalem, saying:
B040C002V002	40	2	2	Where is the newborn king of the Jews? we saw for of him the star in the rising, and are come to do homage of him.
B040C002V003	40	2	3	Having heard and Herod the king was alarmed, and all Jerusalem with him;
B040C002V004	40	2	4	and having called together all the chiefpriests and scribes of the people, he inquired of them where the Anointed should be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	They and said to him: In Bethleem of the Judea; thus for is written by the prophet;
B040C002V006	40	2	6	And thou Bethleem, land of Juda; by no means least art among the princes of Juda; out of thee for shall come forth a prince, who shall govern the people of me, the Israel.
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod privately having called the wisemen, learned exactly from them the time of the appearing a star,
B040C002V008	40	2	8	and sending them into Bethleem, he said: Passing on your way, exactly inquire about the infant; as soon as and you have found, bring word to me, that I also going pay homage to him.
B040C002V009	40	2	9	They and having heard the king departed. And lo, the star, which they saw in the rising, went before them, till going it stood over where was the infant.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	Seeing and the star, they rejoiced a joy very great;
B040C002V011	40	2	11	and being come into the house, they saw the infant with Mary the mother of it, and falling down did homage to it, and opening the treasuries of them, they offered to it gifts, gold and frankincense and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	And being warned in a dream not to return to Herod, by another way they withdrew into the country of them.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	Having withdrawn but of the, lo, a messenger of a Lord appears in a dream to the Joseph, saying: Arising take the infant and the mother of it, and flee into Egypt, and be thou there, till I speak to thee; is about for Herod to seek the infant, to kill it.
B040C002V014	40	2	14	He then arising took the infant and the mother of it by night, and went into Egypt;
B040C002V015	40	2	15	and he was there till the death of Herod; that might be fulfilled the word spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying: Out of Egypt I called the son of me.
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herod seeing that he was mocked by the wisemen, was enraged much; and sending forth he slew all the boys the in Bethleem and in all the borders of her, from two years and under, according to the time which he exactly learnt from the wisemen.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then was fulfilled the word spoken by Jeremiah the prophet, saying:
B040C002V018	40	2	18	A voice in Rama was heard, lamentation and weeping and mourning great; Rachel bewailing the children of her; and not is willing to be comforted because not they are.
B040C002V019	40	2	19	Having died and of the Herod, lo, a messenger of a Lord in a dream appears to the Joseph in Egypt, saying:
B040C002V020	40	2	20	Arising take the infant and the mother of it, and go thou into land Israel; they are dead for the seeking the life of the infant.
B040C002V021	40	2	21	He and arising took the infant and the mother of it, and came into land Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	Hearing and, that Archelaus was reigning over the Judea instead of Herod the father of him, he was afraid there to go; being warned and in a dream, he withdrew into regions of the Galilee.
B040C002V023	40	2	23	And coming he dwelt into a city named Nazareth; that might be fulfilled the words spoken through the prophets, that a Nazarene he will be called.
B040C003V001	40	3	1	In now the days those comes John the dipper, proclaiming in the desert of the Judea, and saying:
B040C003V002	40	3	2	Reform ye; has come nigh for the majesty of the heavens.
B040C003V003	40	3	3	This for is he spoken of by Esaias the prophet, saying: A voice crying out in the desert; make you ready the way of a Lord, straight make ye the beaten tracks of him.
B040C003V004	40	3	4	He and the John had the outer garment of him from hairs of a camel, and a belt made of skin around the loins of him; the and food of him was locusts and honey wild.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then went out to him Jerusalem, and all the Judea, and all the country about of the Jordan;
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and were dipped into the Jordan by him, confessing the sins of them.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	Seeing and many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming to the dipping of him, he said to them: O broods of venomous serpents, who pointed out to you to flee from the coming wrath?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Bring forth then fruit worthy of the reformation,
B040C003V009	40	3	9	and not think to say in yourselves: A father we have the Abraham; I say for to you, that is able the God out of the stones these to raise up children to the Abraham.
B040C003V010	40	3	10	Now and even the axe to the root of the trees lies; every therefore tree not bearing fruit good, is cut down, and into a fire cast.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I indeed dip you in water, into reformation; he but after of me coming, mightier of me is, of whom not I am worthy the sandals to carry; he you will dip in spirit holy and fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	Of whom the winnowing shovel in the hand of him, and he will thoroughly cleanse the threshing floor of him; and he will gather the wheat of him into the storehouse, the but chaff he will burn up in fire inextinguishable.
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then comes the Jesus from the Galilee to the Jordan to the John, of the to be dipped by him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	The but John refused him saying: I need to have by thee to be dipped, and thou comest to me?
B040C003V015	40	3	15	Answering and the Jesus said to him: Permit now; thus for coming it is to us, to fulfil all righteousness. Then he suffered him.
B040C003V016	40	3	16	And having dipped the Jesus went up immediately from the water; and lo, were opened to him the heavens, and was seen the spirit of the God descending like a dove, and coming on him.
B040C003V017	40	3	17	And lo, a voice out of the heavens, saying: This is the son of me the beloved, in whom I delight.
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then the Jesus was led into the desert by the spirit, to be tempted by the accuser.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	And fasting days forty and nights forty, after he was hungry.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	And coming to him the temper, said: If a son thou be of the God, speak, that the stones these loaves may become.
B040C004V004	40	4	4	He but answering said: It is written: Not by bread alone shall live a man; but by every word proceeding from mouth of God.
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then takes him the accuser into the holy city, and places him on the wing of the temple,
B040C004V006	40	4	6	and saying to him: if a son thou be of the God, cast thyself down; it is written for: That to the messengers of him he will give charge of thee; and on hands they shall raise thee, lest thou strikes against a stone the foot of thee.
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Said to him the Jesus: Again it is written: Not thou shalt put to the proof Lord the God of thee.
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again takes him the accuser into a mountain high exceedingly, and shows to him all the kingdoms of the world and the glory of them,
B040C004V009	40	4	9	and says to him: These all to thee I will give, if falling down thou wilt do homage to me.
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Then says to him the Jesus: Go thou behind of me, adversary; it is written for: Lord the God of thee thou shalt worship, and to him only thou shalt render service.
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then leaves him the accuser; and lo, messengers came and ministered to him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	Hearing now the Jesus, that John was delivered up, he withdrew into the Galilee.
B040C004V013	40	4	13	And having left the Nazareth, coming dwelt at Capernaum the by the seaside, in borders of Zabulon and Nephthalim;
B040C004V014	40	4	14	that might be fulfilled the word spoken through Esaias the prophet, saying:
B040C004V015	40	4	15	Land of Zabulon and land Nephthalim way of the sea by the Jordan, Galilee of the nations.
B040C004V016	40	4	16	The people who are sitting in darkness saw a light great; and to those sitting in a region even a shade of death, a light has arisen to them.
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time began the Jesus to proclaim, and to say: Reform; has come nigh for the royal dignity of the heavens.
B040C004V018	40	4	18	Walking and by the sea of the Galilee, he saw two brothers, Simon the called Peter, and Andrew the brother of him, casting a fishingnet into the sea; they were for fishers.
B040C004V019	40	4	19	And he says to them: Come behind of me, and I will make you fishers of men.
B040C004V020	40	4	20	They and immediately leaving the nets, followed him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	And going on from thence, he saw other two brothers, James the of the Zebedee and John the brother of him in the ship with Zebedee of the father of them, mending the nets of them; and called them.
B040C004V022	40	4	22	They and forthwith leaving the ship and the father of them, followed him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	And went about all the Galilee the Jesus, teaching in the synagogues of them, and preaching the glad tidings of the kingdom, and curing every disease and every malady among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	And went the report of him into all the Syria; and they brought to him all the sick having, various diseases and torments seized with, and demoniacs, and lunaties, and paralytics; and he cured them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	And followed to him crowds great from the Galilee, and Decapolis, and from Jerusalem, and Judea, and beyond of the Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	Seeing and the multitudes, he went up to the mountain; and having seated himself, came to him the disciples of him;
B040C005V002	40	5	2	and opening the mouth of him, he taught them, saying:
B040C005V003	40	5	3	Blessed the poor to the spirit; because of them is the kingdom of the heavens.
B040C005V004	40	5	4	Blessed the mourners, for they shall be comforted.
B040C005V005	40	5	5	Blessed the meek, for they shall inherit the earth.
B040C005V006	40	5	6	Blessed the hungering and thirsting the righteousness, for they shall be satisfied.
B040C005V007	40	5	7	Blessed the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.
B040C005V008	40	5	8	Blessed the clean to the heart, for they the God shall see.
B040C005V009	40	5	9	Blessed the peacemakers, for they sons of God shall be called.
B040C005V010	40	5	10	Blessed those being persecuted on account of righteousness, for of them is the kingdom of the heavens.
B040C005V011	40	5	11	Blessed are ye, whenever they reproach you and persecute, and say every evil word against you, speaking falsely, because of me.
B040C005V012	40	5	12	Rejoice ye and exult ye, for the reward of you great in the heavens; in this way for they persecuted the prophets those before you.
B040C005V013	40	5	13	You are the salt of the earth. If but the salt become tasteless, with what shall it be salted? for nothing is it of service any more, except to be cast out, and trodden under foot by the men.
B040C005V014	40	5	14	You are the light of the world. Not possible a city to hide upon a hill being situated;
B040C005V015	40	5	15	nor they light a lamp, and place him under the measure, but on the lampstand; and it gives light to all those in the house.
B040C005V016	40	5	16	Thus let it shine the light of you in the presence of the men, that they may see of you the good works, and may praise the Father of you that in the heavens.
B040C005V017	40	5	17	Not think ye, that I have come to destroy the law or the prophets; not I have come to destroy, but to fulfill.
B040C005V018	40	5	18	Indeed for I say to you, till pass away the heaven and the earth, iota one or one fine point in no wise pass from the law, till all be fulfilled.
B040C005V019	40	5	19	Whoever therefore breaks one of the commandments of these of the least, and teach thus the men, least he shall be called in the kingdom of the heavens; who but ever shall do and teach, the same great shall be called in the kingdom of the heavens.
B040C005V020	40	5	20	I say for to you that except abound the righteousness of you more of the scribes and Pharisees, by no means you may enter into the kingdom of the heavens.
B040C005V021	40	5	21	You have heard, that it was said to the ancients: Not thou kill; who ever shall kill, liable shall be to the tribunal.
B040C005V022	40	5	22	I but say to you, that all the being angry to the brother of him, without cause, liable shall be to the tribunal: who and ever shall say to the brother of him, Vile fellow, liable shall be to the Sanhedrim; who and ever shall say: O fool, liable shall be to the Gehenna of the fire.
B040C005V023	40	5	23	If therefore thou bring the gift of thee of the altar and there remember, that the brother of thee has somewhat against thee,
B040C005V024	40	5	24	leave there the gift of thee before the altar, and go, first be thou reconciled to the brother of thee, and then coming offer the gift of thee.
B040C005V025	40	5	25	Be thou willing to agree with the opponent of thee quickly, while thou art in the way with him; lest thee deliver up the opponent to the judge, and judge thee deliver up to the officer, and into prison thou shalt be cast.
B040C005V026	40	5	26	Indeed I say to thee, by no means thou wilt come out thence, till thou hast paid the last farthing.
B040C005V027	40	5	27	You have heard, that it was said: Not thou shalt commit adultery.
B040C005V028	40	5	28	I but say to you, that all who looking at a woman in order to lust after her, already has debauched her in the heart of him.
B040C005V029	40	5	29	If and the eye of thee the right ensnare thee, tear out it, and cast it from thee, it is profitable for to thee, that should perish one of the members of thee, and not whole the body her, and cast from thee;
B040C005V030	40	5	30	it is profitable for the right of thee hand ensnare thee, cut off her, and cast from thee; it is profitable for to thee that should perish one of the members of thee, and not whole the body of thee should be cast into Gehenna.
B040C005V031	40	5	31	It was said and: that whoever shall release the wife of him, let him give her a bill of divorce.
B040C005V032	40	5	32	I but say to you, that whoever may release the wife of him, except on account of fornication, makes her to commit adultery; and whoever her being divorced, may marry, commits adultery.
B040C005V033	40	5	33	Again you have heard, that it was said to the ancients: Not thou shall swear falsely; shalt perform but to the Lord the oaths of thee.
B040C005V034	40	5	34	I but say to you not swear at all; not even by the heaven, for a throne it is of the God;
B040C005V035	40	5	35	nor by the earth, for a footstool it is of the feet of him; neither by Jerusalem, for a city it is of the great king;
B040C005V036	40	5	36	nor by the head of thee shalt thou swear, for not thou art able one hair white or black to make.
B040C005V037	40	5	37	Let be but the word of you; yes yes; no no; that for over and above of these, of the evil is.
B040C005V038	40	5	38	You have heard, that it was said: An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth.
B040C005V039	40	5	39	I but say to you, not resist the evil; but whoever thee shall slap upon the right of thee cheek, turn to him also the other;
B040C005V040	40	5	40	and to the purposing thee to sue at law, and the tunic of thee to take, give up to him also the mantle;
B040C005V041	40	5	41	and whoever thee shall force to go mile one, go with him two.
B040C005V042	40	5	42	To the asking thee do thou give; and the wishing from thee to borrow money, not do thou repulse.
B040C005V043	40	5	43	You have heard, that it was said: Thou shalt love the neighbor of thee, and hate the enemy of thee.
B040C005V044	40	5	44	I but say to you, love the enemies of you, bless those cursing you, good do to those hating you and pray for those injuring you and persecuting you;
B040C005V045	40	5	45	that you may be sons of the Father of you, of the in heavens; for the sun of him it rises on evil and good, and it rains on just and unjust.
B040C005V046	40	5	46	If for you love those loving you, what reward have you? not even the taxgatherers the same to do?
B040C005V047	40	5	47	and if you salute the brothers of you only, what more do you? not even the Gentiles so do?
B040C005V048	40	5	48	Shall be therefore you perfect, as the Father of you, who in the heavens, perfect is.
B040C006V001	40	6	1	Take heed the righteousness of you not to do in the presence of the men, so as to be exhibited to them; if but otherwise, reward not you have with to the Father of you, to the in the heavens.
B040C006V002	40	6	2	When then thou doest alms, not sound a trumpet in the presence of thee, like the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may have praise of the men. Indeed I say to you, they obtain the reward of them.
B040C006V003	40	6	3	Of thee but doing alms giving, not let it know the left of thee, what does the right of thee,
B040C006V004	40	6	4	that maybe of thee the alms giving in the secret; and the Father of thee, who seeing in the secret, himself will give back to thee.
B040C006V005	40	6	5	And when thou prayest, not thou shalt be like the hypocrites; for they love in the synagogues and Matthew in the corners of the wide places standing to pray, that they may appear to the men. Indeed I say to you, that they have in full the reward of them.
B040C006V006	40	6	6	Thou but, when thou prayest, enter into the retired place of thee, and locking the door of thee, pray thou to the Father of thee, to the in the secret; and the Father of thee, who seeing in the secret place, will give to thee in the clearlight.
B040C006V007	40	6	7	Praying but not babble, like the Gentiles; they imagine for that in the wordiness of them they shall be heard.
B040C006V008	40	6	8	Not therefore you may be like to them; knows for the Father of you, of what things need you have, before of the you ask him.
B040C006V009	40	6	9	In this way then pray you: Father with us, who in the heavens, reverenced the name of thee;
B040C006V010	40	6	10	let come the kingdom of thee; let be done the will of thee, as in heaven, also on the earth;
B040C006V011	40	6	11	the bread of us the sufficient give thou to us today;
B040C006V012	40	6	12	and discharge to us the debts of us, as even we discharge to the debtors of us
B040C006V013	40	6	13	and not bring us into temptation, but save us from the evil.
B040C006V014	40	6	14	If for you forgive to the men the faults of them, will forgive also you the Father of you the heavenly;
B040C006V015	40	6	15	if but not forgive to the men the faults of them, neither the Father of you will forgive the faults of you.
B040C006V016	40	6	16	When and you fast, not be, like the hypocrites, of a sad face; they disfigure for the faces of them; so that they may seem to the men to be fasting. Indeed I say to you, that they obtain the reward of them.
B040C006V017	40	6	17	Thou but fasting anoint of thee the head, and the face of thee wash,
B040C006V018	40	6	18	so that not thou mayest seem to the men fasting, but to the Father of thee, that in the secret; and the Father of thee, who seeing in the secret, will give to thee.
B040C006V019	40	6	19	Not lay up to you treasures on the earth, where moth and rust destroys, and where thieves dig through and steal;
B040C006V020	40	6	20	lay up but to you treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust destroys, and where thieves not dig through nor steal.
B040C006V021	40	6	21	Where for is the treasure of you, there will be also and the heart of you.
B040C006V022	40	6	22	The lamp of the body is the eye. If therefore the eye of thee sound may be, whole the body of thee enlightened will be.
B040C006V023	40	6	23	If but the eye of thee evil may be, whole the body of thee darkness will be. If then the light; that in thee, darkness is, the darkness how great?
B040C006V024	40	6	24	No one is able two lords to serve; either for the one he will hate, and the other he will love; or one he will cling to, and the other he will slight. Not you are able God to serve and mammon.
B040C006V025	40	6	25	For this I say to you: Not be over careful the life of you, what you may eat, and what you may drink; nor to the body of you, what you may put on. Not the life more is the food, and the body the clothing?
