B043C002V012	43	2	12	After this he went down into Capernaum, he and the mother of him, and the brothers of him, and the disciples of him, and there remained not many days.
B043C002V013	43	2	13	And nigh was the passover of the Jews, and went up to Jerusalem the Jesus.
B043C002V014	43	2	14	And he found in the temple those selling oxen and sheep and doves, and the moneychangers sitting.
B043C002V015	43	2	15	And having made a whip out of rushes, all he drove out of the temple, the and sheep and the oxen; and of the moneychangers he poured out the coin, and the tables overturned;
B043C002V016	43	2	16	and to those the doves selling he said: Take these hence; not make you the house of the Father of me a house of merchandise.
B043C002V017	43	2	17	Remembered and the disciples of him, that having been written it is: The zeal of the house of thee will consume me.
B043C002V018	43	2	18	Answered then the Jews and said to him: What sign showest thou to us, that thee thou doest?
