B043C004V006	43	4	6	Was and there a spring of the Jacob. The then Jesus having become weary from the journey, sat down thus over the spring; hour was about six.
B043C004V007	43	4	7	Comes a woman of the Samaria, to draw water. Say to her the Jesus: Give to me a drink.
B043C004V008	43	4	8	(The for disciples of him had gone into the city, that provisions they might buy.)
B043C004V009	43	4	9	Says then to him the woman that Samaritan: How thou, a Jew being, from me to drink askest, being a woman a Samaritan? (Not for associate with Jews Samaritans.)
B043C004V010	43	4	10	Answered Jesus and said to her: If thou hast known the gift of the God, and who is be saying to thee: Give to me to drink; thou wouldst ask him, and he would give thee water living.
B043C004V011	43	4	11	Says to him the woman: O lord, nothing to draw with thou hast, and the well is deep; whence then hast thou the water the living?
B043C004V012	43	4	12	Not thou greater art the father of us, Jacob? who gave to us the well, and he of it drank, and the sons of him, and the cattle of him.
B043C004V013	43	4	13	Answered Jesus and said to her: All the drinking of the water this, will thirst again;
B043C004V014	43	4	14	who but ever may drink of the water, of which I shall give to him, not not may thirst to the age; but the water, which I shall give him, shall be in him a well of water springing into life agelasting.
B043C004V015	43	4	15	Says to him the woman: O lord, give to me this the water, that not I may thirst, nor may come in this place to draw.
B043C004V016	43	4	16	Says to her the Jesus: Go, call the husband of thee, and come here.
B043C004V017	43	4	17	Answered the woman and said: Not I have a husband. Says to her the Jesus: Rightly thou didst say: That a husband not I have.
B043C004V018	43	4	18	Five for husbands thou hast had; and now whom thou hast not is of thee a husband; this truly thou hast said.
B043C004V019	43	4	19	Says to him the woman: O lord, I see, that a prophet art thou.
B043C004V020	43	4	20	The fathers of us in the mountain this worshipped; and you say, that in Jerusalem is the place, where it is necessary to worship.
