B043C004V023	43	4	23	But comes an hour, and now is, when the true worshippers shall worship the Father in spirit and truth; and for the Father such like seeks those worshipping him.
B043C004V024	43	4	24	A spirit the God; and those worshipping him, in spirit and truth it behooves to worship.
B043C004V025	43	4	25	Says to him the woman: I know, that Messiah comes; (the being called Anointed;) when may come he, he will relate to us all.
B043C004V026	43	4	26	Says to her the Jesus: I am, he talking to thee.
B043C004V027	43	4	27	And on this came the disciples of him, and wondered, that with a woman he talked. No one nevertheless said: What seekest thou? or, why talkest thou with her?
B043C004V028	43	4	28	Left therefore the bucket of herself the woman, and went into the city, and says to the men:
B043C004V029	43	4	29	Come you, see a man, who told me all what I did; not this is the Anointed?
B043C004V030	43	4	30	They went out of the city, and were coming to him.
B043C004V031	43	4	31	In and the meantime were asking him the disciples saying: Rabbi, eat.
B043C004V032	43	4	32	He but said to them: I food have to eat, which you not know.
B043C004V033	43	4	33	Said then the disciples to each other: Not any one brought to him food?
