B043C004V035	43	4	35	Not you say, that yet four months it is, and the harvest comes? Lo, I say to you, lift up the eyes of you, and see you the fields, that white they are to harvest already.
B043C004V036	43	4	36	He reaping a reward receives, and gathers fruit for life agelasting; so that both he sowing together may rejoice, and he reaping.
B043C004V037	43	4	37	In for this the word is the true, that one is the sowing, and another the reaping.
B043C004V038	43	4	38	I sent you to reap what you have labored; others labored, and you into the labor of them are entered.
B043C004V039	43	4	39	Out of and the city that many believed into him of the Samaritans, through the word of the woman, testifying: That he told me all what I did.
B043C004V040	43	4	40	When therefore came to him the Samaritans, asking him to abide with them; and he abode there two days.
B043C004V041	43	4	41	And many more believed through the word of him.
B043C004V042	43	4	42	To the and woman they said: That no longer through the they saying we believe; ourselves for we have heard, and we know, that this is truly the savior of the world the Anointed.
B043C004V043	43	4	43	After and the two days he went out thence, and went out into the Galilee.
B043C004V044	43	4	44	Himself for Jesus testified, that a prophet in the own country honor not has.
B043C004V045	43	4	45	When therefore he came into the Galilee, received him the Galileans, all having seen what he did in Jerusalem at the feast; also themselves for came to the feast.
B043C004V046	43	4	46	He came then again into the Cana of the Galilee, where he made the water wine. And was certain courtier, of whom the son was sick, in Capernaum.
B043C004V047	43	4	47	This hearing that Jesus was come out of the Judea into the Galilee, went to him, and was asking him, that he would come down, and heal of him the son; he was about for to die.
B043C004V048	43	4	48	Said therefore the Jesus to him: If not signs and prodigies you may see, not not you may believe.
B043C004V049	43	4	49	Says to him the courtier: O sir, come down, before to die the child of me.
