B043C005V001	43	5	1	After these things was a feast of the Jews, and went up the Jesus to Jerusalem.
B043C005V002	43	5	2	Is now in the Jerusalem, by the sheepgate, a swimming bath, that being called in Hebrew Bethesda, five porches having.
B043C005V003	43	5	3	In these were lying a multitude great of those sick, blind, blame, withered waiting the of the water moving.
B043C005V004	43	5	4	A messenger for at a season went down in the swimmingbath, and agitated the water; he then first stepping in after the agitation of the water, sound became, who indeed was held by disease.
B043C005V005	43	5	5	Was and a certain man there, thirty and eight years being in the feeble health.
B043C005V006	43	5	6	This seeing the Jesus lying, and knowing that long already time he had been, he says to him: Do thou wish sound to become?
B043C005V007	43	5	7	Answered him he sick being: O sir, a man not I have, that when may be agitated the water, he may put me into the swimmingbath; in which but am coming I, another before me goes down.
B043C005V008	43	5	8	Says to him the Jesus: Rise, take up the bed of thee, and walk.
B043C005V009	43	5	9	And immediately became sound the man, and took up the bed of himself, and walked. It was and a sabbath in that the day.
B043C005V010	43	5	10	Said then the Jews to the having been healed: A sabbath it is; not it is lawful for thee to carry the bed.
B043C005V011	43	5	11	He answered them: He having made a sound, he to me said: Take up the bed of thee, and walk.
B043C005V012	43	5	12	They asked then him: Who is the man, he saying to thee: Take up the bed of thee, and walk?
B043C005V013	43	5	13	He but having been cured not knew who it is; the for Jesus slipped out, a crowd being in the place.
B043C005V014	43	5	14	After these finds him the Jesus in the temple, and said to him: See, sound thou hast become; no longer do thou sin, that so worse to thee anything may happen.
B043C005V015	43	5	15	Went away the man, and told to the Jews, that Jesus it is, he having made him sound.
B043C005V016	43	5	16	And through this persecuted the Jesus the Jews, because these he did in a sabbath.
B043C005V017	43	5	17	The and Jesus answered them: The father of me till now works, and I work.
B043C005V018	43	5	18	Through this therefore more sought him the Jews to kill, because not only he was breaking the sabbath, but also a Father his own said the God, equal himself making to the God.
B043C005V019	43	5	19	Answered then the Jesus and said to them: Indeed indeed I say to you, not is able the son to do of himself nothing, if not anything he may see the Father doing; what for ever he may do, these also the son in like manner does.
B043C005V020	43	5	20	The for Father loves the son, and all shows to him, what he does; and greater of these shows to him works, so that you may wonder.
B043C005V021	43	5	21	As for the Father raises the dead ones and makes alive; thus also the son, whom he will, makes alive.
B043C005V022	43	5	22	Not even for the Father judges any one; but the judgment all has given to the son;
B043C005V023	43	5	23	so that all may honor the son, even as they honor the Father. He not honoring the son, not honors the Father, that having sent him.
B043C005V024	43	5	24	Indeed indeed I say to you, that he the word of me hearing, and believing, the having sent me has life agelasting, and into judgment not comes, but has passed out of the death into the life.
B043C005V025	43	5	25	Indeed indeed I say to you, that comes an hour, and now is, when the dead ones shall hear the voice of the son of the God; and those having heard will live.
B043C005V026	43	5	26	As for the Father has life in himself; so he gave also the son life to have in himself.
B043C005V027	43	5	27	And authority he gave to him also judgment to execute, because a son of man he is.
B043C005V028	43	5	28	Not wonder you this; because comes an hour, in which all those in the tombs, shall hear the voice of him,
B043C005V029	43	5	29	and shall come forth, those the good things having done, to a resurrection of life; those and the evil things having done, to a resurrection of judgment.
B043C005V030	43	5	30	Not am able I to do of myself nothing. Even as I hear, I judge, and the judgment the mine just is; that not I seek the will the mine, but the will of the sending me.
B043C005V031	43	5	31	If I testify concerning myself, the testimony of me out not is true.
B043C005V032	43	5	32	Another is he testifying concerning me; and I know, that rue is the testimony, which he testifies concerning me.
B043C005V033	43	5	33	You have sent to John, and he has testified to the truth.
