B043C006V001	43	6	1	After these things went the Jesus over the sea that of Galilee, of the Tiberias.
B043C006V002	43	6	2	And was following him a crowd great, because they saw the signs, which he was doing on those being sick.
B043C006V003	43	6	3	Went and into the mountain the Jesus, and there he was sitting with the disciples of himself.
B043C006V004	43	6	4	Was and near the passover, the feast of the Jews.
B043C006V005	43	6	5	Lifted up then the Jesus the eyes, and seeing that great a crowd was coming to him, says to the Philip: Whence shall we buy loaves, that may eat these?
B043C006V006	43	6	6	(This but he said trying him; he for knew, what he was about to do.)
B043C006V007	43	6	7	Answered him Philip: Two hundred denarii of loaves not are enough for them, so that each of them a little may take.
B043C006V008	43	6	8	Says to him one of the disciples of him, Andrew, the brother of Simon Peter:
B043C006V009	43	6	9	Is little boy one here, who has five loaves barley, and two small fishes; but these what are for so many?
B043C006V010	43	6	10	Said and the Jesus: Make you the men to recline. Was and grass much in the place. Reclined therefore the men the number about five thousand.
B043C006V011	43	6	11	Took and the loaves the Jesus, and having thanks distributed to the disciples, the and disciples to those reclining; in like manner also of the fishes what they wished.
B043C006V012	43	6	12	When and they were filled, he says to the disciples of himself: Collect the remaining fragments, so that not any may be lost.
B043C006V013	43	6	13	They collected therefore, and filled twelve baskets of fragments, out of the five loaves of the barley, which remained to those having eaten.
B043C006V014	43	6	14	The therefore men seeing what did a sign the Jesus, said: That this is truly the prophet, he coming into the world.
